      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TIGERLICIOUS (9) is going well having missed by just a head two starts ago at this circuit and distance before a commendable second last time out at Newcastle. May need an ounce of luck from the back row but looks close to a win. LOUISE LUCK (6) made a winning start for the Seaton Grima yard when she came from this barrier and dug deep to get home narrowly at Menangle. That was her first hitout for five weeks so it should have improved her. Big chance again. BIRDY GAL (4) has been going around at Menangle of late and did a good job to come from this barrier and finish less than 5m off the winner last start. Had a month off since but was kept up to the mark with a trial. LOOKIN GOOD MARGIE (5) returns to the front row and is capable of better than what she has been showing of late.",
